        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 1:54PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 10 miles west of Carpenter to over
Rockport, or extending from 17 miles southeast of Cheyenne to 19
miles south of Cheyenne, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockport, Carr and Hereford.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
